<title>GREECE: CITIBANK CUTS MORTGAGE RATES BY 50 BASIS POINTS.</title>
<headline>CITIBANK CUTS MORTGAGE RATES BY 50 BASIS POINTS.</headline>
<dateline>ATHENS 1996-12-23</dateline>
<text>
<p>Citibank will cut its mortgage</p>
<p>rate by 50 basis points down to 16.75 percent but leave its base</p>
<p>lending rates unchanged for a week effective on Tuesday, it said</p>
<p>in a statement.</p>
<p>Citibank, which reviews its rates weekly, offers the</p>
<p>following rate structure:</p>
<p>** Base rate for working capital loans at 18.25 percent</p>
<p>** Business and professional base lending rate at 19 percent</p>
<p>** Base rate for freely investible funds at 18.50 percent</p>
<p>** Mortgage rate at 16.75 percent from 17.25</p>
<p>** Personal installment loans at 24 percent</p>
<p>** Personal installment loans with invoices at 23 percent</p>
<p>** Auto loans at 19.75 percent</p>
<p>Contribution under Law 128 is not included in the rates</p>
<p>quoted, it said.</p>
<p>Rates on working capital loans in foreign currency for the</p>
<p>coming week will be:</p>
<p>    US Dollars     :  8.09 percent</p>
<p>    Marks	    :  5.75 percent</p>
<p>    Yen		:  2.80 percent</p>
<p>    Guilders	 :  5.59 percent</p>
<p>    Ecu		:  6.71 percent</p>
<p>Pounds Sterling:  8.99 percent</p>
<p>French francs  :  5.93 percent</p>
<p>Citibank's deposit rates will have as follows:</p>
<p>Base savings rate: 10.75 percent</p>
<p>Gold-Plus account:  8.0  percent (0-5 million drs)</p>
<p>			     12.5  percent (5-30 million drs)</p>
<p>			     13.0  percent (30-80 million drs)</p>
<p>			     13.5  percent (over 80 million drs)</p>
<p>    Save-plus-12:	10.75 percent (0-5 million drs)</p>
<p>			     11.75 percent (over 5 million drs)</p>
<p>--George Georgiopoulos, Athens Newsroom +301 3311812-4</p>
